1. *Izlazak* iz kuće je bio otežan zbog snega. (Going out of the house was difficult because of the snow.)
2. Oni su planirali *izlazak* u grad već nedeljama. (They have been planning a night out in the city for weeks.)
3. Kada je videla *izlazak* sunca, osetila se mnogo bolje. (When she saw the sunrise, she felt much better.)
4. Njegov *izlazak* na scenu bio je spektakularan. (His entrance onto the stage was spectacular.)
5. Uprkos lošem vremenu, odlučili su se za *izlazak* u prirodu. (Despite the bad weather, they decided to go out into nature.)
6. Žao mi je, propustila sam tvoj *izlazak* na televiziji sinoć. (I'm sorry, I missed your appearance on TV last night.)
7. Njihov *izlazak* iz restorana je izazvao veliku pažnju medija. (Their exit from the restaurant attracted a lot of media attention.)
8. Tvoj *izlazak* iz sobe me je probudio sinoć. (Your leaving the room woke me up last night.)

Note: The word "izlazak" is translated as "going out," "night out," "sunrise," "entrance," "outing," "appearance," "exit," and "leaving" in these sentences.